Class YahooMediaText

Represents a means of allowing the inclusion of a text transcript, closed captioning, or lyrics of the media content.

Inheritance

Namespace: Argotic.Extensions.Core
Assembly: Argotic.Extensions.dll
Syntax
[Serializable]
public class YahooMediaText : IComparable
Remarks

Many of these YahooMediaText objects are permitted to provide a time series of text. In such cases, it is encouraged, but not required, that the YahooMediaText objects be grouped by language and appear in time sequence order based on the start time. YahooMediaText objects can have overlapping start and end times.

End

Gets or sets the end time offset that this text stops being relevant to the media object.

Declaration
public TimeSpan End { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.TimeSpan

A System.TimeSpan that represents the end time offset that this text stops being relevant to the media object. The default value is System.TimeSpan.MinValue, which indicates that no end time was specified.
Remarks

If this property is not provided, and a Start is used, it is expected that the End is either the end of the clip or the start of the next YahooMediaText object.

Language

Gets or sets the primary language encapsulated in this media object.

Declaration
public CultureInfo Language { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.Globalization.CultureInfo

A System.Globalization.CultureInfo that represents the natural or formal language in which the Content is written. The default value is a null reference, which indicates no language was specified.
Remarks

The value of this property is a language identifier as defined by RFC 3066: Tags for the Identification of Languages, or its successor.
